Controversial Durban businessman Thoshan Panday's mother has appeared in court in connection with the World Cup police accommodation tender fraud case. Mawande Kheswa reports. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Controversial Durban businessman Thoshan Panday's mother has appeared in court. This is in connection with the World Cup police accommodation tender fraud case. READ: Thoshan Panday's deals with police scrutinised Panday and his three co-accused allegedly committed fraud amounting to R47-million. Now his 69-year-old mother, Arvenda, has appeared with three other family members in the Durban magistrate's court on fraud, corruption, money laundering and racketeering charges. * eNCA's Mawande Kheswa reports.